        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         The whole HP thing didn't really become a problem until level 49, and Lich just seems to burn life away insanely fast if you are looming around 700-1000 hps (me) at 49.  </P><P>At 60, with Arch Lich, it's the same deal.  I was around 1650 self buffed, and it burned through my health very quickly.  Right now, I am just less than 1900 self buffed, and it's starting to seem a little better... I am hoping by the end of July to be nearing 2100 self buffed, as I finish up my Chardok quests....</P><P>So, I say start building your HP collection as you near 49, but really post 40 you should do it as soon as possible.  Dont wait till the last minute like me.  :)</P><P>Xuraz Xorthexia - <BR>Warlock<BR>Xegony Server<BR>Profile - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
