        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         A couple of items can really boost your hps.  Get the 6ac/65hp rings (or even 5ac/55hp rings, if finances are tight).  A spider fur belt and a Coterie General's cape.  These 4 items will boost your hps by over 200.  HPs become more critical at higher levels, but try to keep your int over 190.  The whole HP argument is based on mana regeneration/hp loss, but it never hurts to have a large mana pool.</P><P>Sta?  Not too much effect on hps before level 50.  So, Sta at level 23? Insignificant.  700+ hp at level 23, your a poor tank unless you also have a good mana pool.  Of course, Nephylum seems to be the ultimate twink, with gear a level 50 necro would drool over.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
