        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         WTG Tauruse</P><P>Finally an intelligent formula for the ancient hp versus int argument.</P><P>One point that I would like to make to all those necros that seem to buy into the STA &gt; INT argument is this.</P><P>As a level 60 erudite necro each point of Sta that I get grants me a mere 2.444444 extra HP. There is just no way that I am going to take an STA item over an INT item unless my INT is totally maxed.</P><P>The absolute bottom line on this entire argument has to be that without MANA we can't cast spells. We do not get mana from HP, we get mana from INT. We can indirectly convert our HP to mana, provided we have the INT to support the mana. But if our INT is too low there is just no way we can get a large enough mana to to effectively cast our spells.</P><P>Tauruse formula is really the best I have ever seen. Don't waste your time getting HP / STA items unless your mana pool is big enough to cast 8 level approporate spells without going OOM.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
