         Yes I would like to agree with Sally and Taruse. I am 25hp away from breaking the 2k mark self buffed. There's very little left for me to buy that can boost me much more so I will have to wait my chance to loot a few more bits of SS armor or other nice trinkets. I look at a few profiles and see a lot of dragon gear which is out of my guild's reach for the time being as well as being the sort of stuff that a lot of other classes would get before I would. I have a mana pool just over 3100 and this is the stat I want to increase more than HP if I can. Why? I do a lot of raiding these days and for much of the time I am unable to sit and med. I can get over 3k hp with Aego so I need to look for more mana/int items to boost my manapool more than anything. Keep a balance and work to your playstyle.</P><P>Abaraxas Malfoy<BR>Warlock of the Tribunal<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
