         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>So basically, before level 44 your primary concern should be getting your INT up toward and above 200<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>I would disagree.  There are a lot of dungeons for lower and mid level players now, and a lot of places in those where a necro puller is a real boon.  If you are pulling then you'll need as many hp's as you can get, whatever level.</P><P>If you don't pull or get beaten on much then by all means go for that 200 int.  But I've gone through most of my levels with 110 int, just gone up to 145 now, and I've hardly ever gone oom in a group.  It's not like you can cast more over time with more int anyway /shrug.</P><P>Rakis (<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=215309" target="_blank">Magelo</a>)<BR>37th level Necro<BR>UK resident of <a href="http://pub96.ezboard.com/bkanebaylecommunitycenter" target="_blank">Kane Bayle</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
